Package org.jpws.data

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    OptionChangeListener
    Interface for listeners to option change events issued from static class "Options".
    PersistentOptions  
    PWDatabase
    Not used in this release.
    PWDatabaseClass
    Not used in this release.
    PWDB_RecordHandle
    Not used in this release.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Exchange
    Class describing various elements for communicating records and data fields of a database with a serializable text form for export and import features of the program.
    Exchange.DataField
    This class represents a datafield of a database record in its generic plane.
    Exchange.FieldSet
    Class to represent a set of DataField instances.
    Exchange.RecordSet
    Class to represent a set of records, represented by their UUID.
    IOManager
    IOManager has two principal functions: A) it regulates access to file IO on a generic level in order to prevent destructive conflicts, and B) it serves as a cache for PWS database files and regulates access to their persistent states (external files).
    IOManager.MonitorPanel  
    LoggingPrintStream
    LoggingPrintStream provides multiplex function to a logging print stream.
    OptionChangeEvent
    Type for a single option change event.
    Options
    Static singleton class to provide and persistently store program options.
    PwsFileSocket
    A containment structure for a PwsFile to deal with backend tasks.
    PwsFileSocket.BackupManager
    Organises automatic backups for PwsFiles in PwsFileSocket objects.
    PwsFileSocket.ChangeEvent
    Class for events which are thrown to indicate alterations in the enclosing class'es operation properties.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IO_OverrunException
    Exception thrown when function access is denied to a thread because of a critical state of the application in general or specific to a particular IO-destination.
    IOManager.OperationLockedException  
    JPWS_Exception  
    UndefinedPersistencyException
    Exception thrown to indicate that a required definition of a persistency state of an object is not existent.
    UserBreakException
